Example 1: a method that returns the sum of two integers 

# Informal Pseudo-Code

- Prompt the user to enter two integers.
- Get input from user and validate that input is an integer. If so, assign it to a variable. Repeat. 
- Add the two integers and assign the sum to a variable. 
- Return the value of the sum.


# Formal Psuedo-Code

START

PRINT "Enter the first integer you'd like to add."
GET number from user
Validate that input == integer
SET number1 = input from user

PRINT "Enter the second integer you'd like to add."
GET number from user
Validate that input == integer
SET number2 = input from user

SET sum = number1 + number2
PRINT sum

END
